<h3>Introduction</h3>

<p>Those who had read Ponniyin Selvan written by Kalki would have numerous questions. As with any history novel, Ponniyin Selvan also blended with Facts and Fictions, and people have been reading lot of history books, store inscriptions (Kalvettu) and trying to figure out what happened and what was on Kalki's mind when he penned this great epic novel.</p>
<p>Thiru. S.Gokul on 2003 written series of article on Facts, Fictions and Characters which were published in Yahoo Groups. And it has been formatted and republished here with his permission. </p>
